DESCRIPTION:This course introduces students to major topics in general biol
 ogy. This courses focuses on the principles of structure and function of l
 iving things at the molecular\, cellular and organismic levels of organiza
 tion. Major topics included are introduction to the scientific process\, c
 hemistry of cells\, organization of cells\, cellular respiration\, photosy
 nthesis\, cell division\, genetics\, DNA replication\, transcription\, and
  translation. May be repeated up to 1 credit. Prerequisite: MATH 1215 or h
 igher\, and a C- or better in (CHEM 1120G or CHEM 1215G or CHEM 1216). Pre
 requisite/Corequisite: BIOL 2110G.
